result.execSummary:
The defendant Tammy J Carlson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Retail Theft - Intentionally Take (<=$500) [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.50(1m)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Tammy J Carlson in court with Attorney Claire Zyber.   District Attorney's Office Law Intern Barry Braatz appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count #1.   Court performs plea colloquy and finds Defendant guilty of Count #1.  State gives sentencing recommendations.  Attorney Zyber makes statements regarding sentencing.  Court sentences the Defendant to the following:

COUNT #1:    IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

120 DAYS STRAIGHT TIME (CREDIT -  5 days)

TERM OF PROBATION:  1 YEAR     **Transfer allowed to Milwaukee County**

CONDITIONS OF PROBATON:  
____Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
____No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs 
____No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
____Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are 
prescribed.
____Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
____No contact with: Kohl's stores

COSTS:  $253.00 & $200.00 DNA surcharge  (to be paid as a condition of probation)

**Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided, immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.**
